song_title: I Said What I Am (Female, Hip-Hop)
lyrics_snippet: I know what I’m building. Even when they tear me down
Is it peace or just pretend? I’m tired of borrowing moods

I wasn’t left out—I feel right
Not every room deserves my light
You were the storm that tore through fast. But I’m the sky that always lasts. Still wide, still blue, still brave, still bright. I carry calm, I hold my light.

My World, My Say
My World, My Say
My World, My Say
My World, My Say
My World, My Say
We shape the world by what we say.
We shape the world by what we say.
We shape the world by what we say.
We shape the world by what we say.
Just learning the map that leads to you. No need to impress, no need to bend—Just tell me that story again.
I planned the whole thing in my head. I’d say “hey” real chill, then nod instead.
I left you a note, didn’t sign my name. But it’s tucked in your book, like a gentle flame. It says “You’re kind” and “I see you there”
You dropped your pen, I gave it back. Said, “No big deal,” then overreacted. Inside I’m screaming “That was smooth…”. But outside I’m just me + you
I don’t need flowers or big displays. Just look at me that certain way. I show my care in lowercase. Like staying late, like knowing your pace.

song_title: Yeah, I Noticed (POV_ The girl who sees through the act)
lyrics_snippet: You don’t have to say you’re brave. I already saw you try. It’s not the words that made me smile—It’s the trying.
If I listened with more grace, with less reply, Would your heart stay close instead of saying goodbye?

I don’t need you to fix the rain
Just stay close when I’m hiding pain

I don’t need you to fix the rain
Just stay close when I’m hiding pain

If we both reach out
We could find each other in the light
Some days don’t shine. But I still keep time. I don’t glow, I don’t shout. But I still know what I’m about
Too much rain, too many shoulds, Advice that comes in endless drifts. They only need a quiet sound, A gentle hand, a steady ground
But when they fall, I lift them high, Like springs that push toward the sky. Bounce them forward, let them soar, Yet I remain—a bed with springs.
I won’t trade my stars for stone  Or lose my voice to feel less alone . What’s rare is still a song unsaid, I’m proud to wear the uncommon thread.

You say, ‘Leave me alone,’ 
but I hear ‘Please don’t go’

I held your hand, but missed your heart
I stayed close, but felt apart
If I could go back, I’d learn to stay
Not just with love—but in your way

So I say thanks, for the love I know, 
In the little ways that help me grow. 
Parents, friends, and teachers too, 
And myself — for pulling through.

Step in the class, don’t just sit in the row,  
Ask one thing that’ll make your mind grow.  
“Why this? How that?” — let the sparks fly,  
Even small questions can open up the sky.

One spark, one spark — light it every day,  
Ask one question, find a brand-new way.
